{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1498602,"duration_api_ms":113385,"ttft_ms":2538,"ttft_stream_ms":2061,"time_to_request_ms":528,"num_turns":21,"result":"Task complete. The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is deployed and fully functional.\n\n## Summary\n\nDeployed a 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.1 cluster in the `elasticsearch` namespace using only native Kubernetes resources (no CRDs/operators):\n\n- **ConfigMap `es-config`** — `elasticsearch.yml` with security + HTTP/transport TLS enabled, using the existing `es-http-tls` secret certs; discovery via the headless service and `initial_master_nodes: es-0,es-1,es-2`.\n- **StatefulSet `es`** (3 replicas) — image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1`, `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` from the `elastic-password` secret, TLS secret mounted at `config/certs`, per-pod PVCs, and an init container setting `vm.max_map_count`.\n- **Service `es-http`** — ClusterIP exposing HTTPS on port 9200.\n- **Headless Service `es-discovery`** (with `publishNotReadyAddresses`) for node discovery, plus a **PDB** (`minAvailable: 2`).\n\n### Two issues fixed during bring-up\n1. **Bootstrap deadlock** — default ordered StatefulSet startup meant es-0 could never become Ready (it needs all 3 masters to form a cluster) and so es-1/es-2 were never created. Fixed with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`.\n2. **Broken readiness probe** — an unquoted `&` in the health-check URL backgrounded curl in the shell, so the probe always failed even though the cluster was green. Fixed by quoting the URL.\n\n### Verification (through the `es-http` Service)\n- Cluster health: **green, 3 nodes, 3 data nodes**.\n- All pods `1/1 Ready`.\n- **Write** succeeded (`\"result\":\"created\"`).\n- **Read** returned the document (`\"found\": true`).\n\nManifest saved at `stage_01/es.yaml`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"8cc9ceef-319d-4bd1-a165-7cabda83c05c","total_cost_usd":0.8036695000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":